Suspected militiamen killed nine civilians overnight Monday in the troubled east of the Democratic Republic of Congo, government officials and the military said. The massacre occurred in the town of Oicha, in the Beni region, local administrator Donat Kibwana told AFP. The assailants were suspected members of the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF), an armed group blamed for hundreds of killings since 2014.   Victims identified as one sergeant and three privates Expert report blasts Malian's leadership and demands his removal Juba House committee confirms the environmental contamination in former Unity State